<subSubSection pageId="107" pageNumber="386" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="107.[741,1334,2900,3323]" lastBlockId="107.[129,1331,3328,3479]" pageId="107" pageNumber="386">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goodwin" authorityYear="1932" box="[742,1005,3053,3086]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="107" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tropicalis">Peromyscus tropicalis</taxonomicName>
is in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1139,1271,3053,3086]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="107" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicanus">mexicanus</taxonomicName>
species group. It was initially described as subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1898" box="[948,1165,3132,3165]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="107" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="guatemalensis">P. guatemalensis</taxonomicName>
, but it was later placed in synonomy with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Saussure" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1169,1334,3172,3205]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="107" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mexicanus">P. mexicanus</taxonomicName>
saxatilis. Recent DNA studies suggest that some of what historically was recognized as P. g. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goodwin" authorityYear="1932" box="[845,957,3290,3323]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="107" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tropicalis">tropicalis</taxonomicName>
or P. m. saxatilis should be considered a distinct species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goodwin" authorityYear="1932" box="[545,692,3328,3361]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="107" pageNumber="386" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tropicalis">P. tropicalis</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
